articles.summary: French in space transportation company Exotrail is launching two U S based subsidiaries one focused specifically on serving U S government and defense customers the company said Monday. Tyler Browder co founder and former head of satellite software developer Kubos was installed to lead the new ExotRail U S Inc. articles.title: Array Labs is scanning the Earth from space to equip autonomous vehicles with 3D maps | TechCrunch
articles.description: Array Labs is planning on scanning the Earth in 3D, data that can be used for autonomous vehicle development, augmented reality and more.
articles.content: Its an ofttold story the boom of space startups today can be traced to dramatically lowered cost in launch and satellite manufacturing over the past ten years. But Array Labs, a twoyearold startu [+3967 chars]
articles.summary: Array Labs plans to map Earth in D by flying clusters of radar satellites in low Earth orbit to image the same place at the same time. The company hopes to capture a full high resolution D digital record of the world. The data will be of such high resolution to be used by driverless vehicle fleets AR headsets insurance analytics and in national security applications. Array will launch its first test satellite on a SpaceX ride share mission next year the first in a series of test satellites designed to iteratively de risk different aspects of the company s technology.
